OL,7,F"We are absolutely right to say it is
OL,8,Fnot good enough that 2.8 million
OL,9,Fpeople have been written off out of
OL,10,Fthe work place due to long term
OL,11,Fsickness, a million young people not
OL,12,Fin education, employment or training.
OL,14,F"We have to make sure those people
OL,15,Fhave the chances and choices they
OL,16,Fdeserve to work".
OL,18,FKendall insisted "being written off
OL,19,Fand having a life on benefits is not
OL,20,Fgood".
